WEBVTT

00:00:22.539 --> 00:00:28.140
We extend a warm welcome to all who accepted an invitation to join us for this convention.

00:00:29.739 --> 00:00:34.140
We live in an unfriendly world where true friends are hard to find.

00:00:35.179 --> 00:00:39.420
Is it possible to draw close to God and have him as our friend?

00:00:39.740 --> 00:00:43.619
If so, what must we do to gain God's friendship?

00:00:44.859 --> 00:00:51.380
Brother Kenneth Cook, a member of the governing body, will answer those questions in the discourse entitled

00:00:51.380 --> 00:00:55.859
Friendship with God. How possible.

00:01:04.790 --> 00:01:08.390
Is it realistic to believe that you can be a friend with God?

00:01:09.269 --> 00:01:13.510
If until now you've answered no to that question, please consider this.

00:01:14.469 --> 00:01:19.829
The lives of millions of people today prove that friendship with God is possible.

00:01:20.549 --> 00:01:24.709
Their lives prove that we can find a peaceful and meaningful life now,

00:01:25.269 --> 00:01:28.790
as well as hope for never lasting and peaceful future.

00:01:29.989 --> 00:01:35.590
If you desire that for yourself and others, we urge you to listen to this scriptural talk.

00:01:36.950 --> 00:01:42.629
We emphasize the need to listen because many people ignore that important question,

00:01:42.629 --> 00:01:45.989
that is, can you be a friend with God?

00:01:47.030 --> 00:01:50.549
Why is it that many put such an important question out of their mind?

00:01:51.189 --> 00:01:57.109
There are a number of reasons. For example, some believe that God is impersonal or unknowable,

00:01:57.750 --> 00:02:01.109
or that He does not exist and that He's not interested in humans.

00:02:01.909 --> 00:02:07.430
They are taught that God is a mystery and that He is cruel, harsh, and demanding.

00:02:08.629 --> 00:02:13.990
Many religious leaders claim that God will punish bad people forever in a place of torment.

00:02:14.870 --> 00:02:17.990
Do you feel drawn into friendship with a God like that?

00:02:18.870 --> 00:02:20.949
Who in their right mind would?

00:02:21.909 --> 00:02:26.710
Still, other people, after seeing all of the injustice and suffering in the world,

00:02:26.710 --> 00:02:31.349
have concluded that God must be dead, or that He never existed at all.

00:02:32.469 --> 00:02:36.949
And then there are those who believe that they have done too many bad things in their life

00:02:36.949 --> 00:02:39.750
to ever be a friend of God.

00:02:41.349 --> 00:02:44.629
Do any of those causes for doubt or concern apply to you?

00:02:45.509 --> 00:02:51.750
If so, please listen carefully to the following four key points that may help you to see

00:02:51.750 --> 00:02:56.550
that friendship with God is truly possible. We will then develop each one.

00:02:57.509 --> 00:03:01.669
First, we'll look at how sin separates us from God.

00:03:02.550 --> 00:03:07.509
Second, we'll look at how God has taken the initiative to heal the breach

00:03:07.509 --> 00:03:10.870
and bring obedient humans back into friendship with Him.

00:03:11.830 --> 00:03:18.069
Then, we'll examine what we can do to become God's friend in an everlasting way.

00:03:18.870 --> 00:03:24.870
And finally, we will consider how friendship with God brings peace now and in the future.

00:03:25.909 --> 00:03:33.669
So, for our first point, what is it that separates us from God in a word sin?

00:03:34.870 --> 00:03:36.389
Why does sin separate us?

00:03:37.189 --> 00:03:43.990
Because the true God is holy. He's pure, and his conduct is perfect.

00:03:43.990 --> 00:03:48.229
He does not have a trace of sin. He's clean and the highest sense.

00:03:48.949 --> 00:03:53.830
No human can be holy to that degree, not even close.

00:03:54.789 --> 00:04:00.389
To illustrate, consider the words human and imperfect. They go together, don't they?

00:04:00.389 --> 00:04:04.229
You cannot fully describe humans without mentioning imperfection.

00:04:04.789 --> 00:04:10.229
It's just a part of us, and human history shows this to be sadly and painfully true.

00:04:11.349 --> 00:04:17.509
So then, our sins or imperfections create a barrier between us and God.

00:04:18.389 --> 00:04:25.750
This separation is described at Isaiah chapter 59 and verse 2 where we are told in part.

00:04:27.350 --> 00:04:33.990
Your own errors have separated you from your God. Your sins have made him hide his face

00:04:33.990 --> 00:04:43.350
from you. Separated from God, it says, we were born into this state, but God did not create us to

00:04:43.350 --> 00:04:51.269
be sinful. Our sins are not his fault. The first humans, Adam and Eve, were created perfect,

00:04:51.829 --> 00:04:58.069
but they proved to be ungrateful and selfish, and they rejected God's friendship.

00:04:58.870 --> 00:05:04.470
They destroyed their peace with God by sinning against him, and they became his enemies.

00:05:05.350 --> 00:05:12.149
Adam then passed sin on to his descendants as well as death. We read about this terrible

00:05:12.149 --> 00:05:21.990
inheritance at Romans chapter 5 and verse 12. In this verse, the Apostle Paul summarizes why

00:05:22.470 --> 00:05:30.230
inherited sinful condition leads to death. He wrote, that is why just as through one man sin entered

00:05:30.230 --> 00:05:39.350
into the world and death through sin, and so death spread to all men because they had all sinned.

00:05:40.870 --> 00:05:51.509
Death spread to all men. This pandemic of sin has a 100% infection rate and a 100% mortality rate.

00:05:52.069 --> 00:05:58.949
No human can escape it. As Paul said, death spread because they had all sinned.

00:06:00.149 --> 00:06:06.790
On our own, we cannot correct our sinful state. It's as if we have fallen into a deep pit

00:06:06.790 --> 00:06:13.990
with seemingly no way out. But are we left without hope? No. In fact, although God views some

00:06:13.990 --> 00:06:21.910
people as his enemies, he treats others as his friends. For example, regarding the man Abraham,

00:06:21.910 --> 00:06:28.709
the Bible book of James says in chapter 2 and verse 23, that Abraham put faith in Jehovah,

00:06:29.269 --> 00:06:38.310
and it was counted to him as righteousness, and he came to be called Jehovah's friend. Abraham

00:06:38.310 --> 00:06:45.430
was as imperfect as we are, but he came to be called God's friend. What has God done to make it

00:06:45.430 --> 00:06:54.470
possible for humans to gain his favor and blessing? Simply put, our Creator has taken the initiative.

00:06:54.470 --> 00:07:00.389
He has taken steps to heal the breach that was caused by sin and to eliminate the separation

00:07:00.389 --> 00:07:08.790
between us and him. How has he done this? First, the Holy Scriptures tell us that God desires for

00:07:08.790 --> 00:07:14.870
us to come to know him and to be at peace with him. In fact, he appeals to us to do this.

00:07:15.750 --> 00:07:23.269
In the Bible book of Acts chapter 17 and verse 27, we are told that God wants us to sincerely

00:07:23.269 --> 00:07:29.589
seek him, and that if we do, we will find that he's not far off from each one of us.

00:07:30.870 --> 00:07:37.990
Next, and very important, God took the initiative to make this possible by providing the sacrifice of

00:07:37.990 --> 00:07:46.709
his Son Jesus in order to redeem us from sin. That was an unparalleled act of love.

00:07:47.829 --> 00:07:54.709
As we now read 1 John chapter 4 and verse 10, please think about what it says regarding this

00:07:54.709 --> 00:08:02.709
matchless act of love on God's part, and so that we may never forget that God took the initiative

00:08:02.790 --> 00:08:09.350
to heal the breach, so to speak. 1 John 4 10 says, the love is in this respect,

00:08:09.990 --> 00:08:18.790
not that we have loved God, but that he loved us and sent his Son as a propitiatory sacrifice

00:08:18.790 --> 00:08:29.110
for our sins. What did God do? God loved us, it says, and he sent his Son. This sacrifice that

00:08:29.110 --> 00:08:35.990
God provided by means of his Son is called propitiatory because it can atone for our sins,

00:08:35.990 --> 00:08:43.509
and here is how it can do so. What Jesus gave in sacrifice for us was equal to what Adam lost

00:08:43.509 --> 00:08:52.870
for us, that is a perfect human life. Adam exchanged his perfect life for death by his rebellion

00:08:52.870 --> 00:09:00.470
against God. As mentioned earlier, Adam then passed sin onto his descendants, and he placed

00:09:00.470 --> 00:09:07.110
this on a path outside of God's friendship. On the other hand, the death of Jesus allowed for

00:09:07.110 --> 00:09:13.669
a ransom, or a means to satisfy God's justice so that we could receive back what Adam lost for us.

00:09:14.629 --> 00:09:21.830
That undeserved gift from God was given a great cost, clearly our Creator wants us to come to know

00:09:22.549 --> 00:09:29.830
and to enjoy a beautiful friendship with Him. We should be very grateful that God took the necessary

00:09:29.830 --> 00:09:39.350
step to close the gap and provide a way for us to become his friend. The next step involves each of us,

00:09:39.990 --> 00:09:48.789
what is required of us, humility. We must be humble enough to accept God's gift. If we are humble,

00:09:48.789 --> 00:09:55.029
we'll see our need for God's mercy, and we'll then do our part to show appreciation.

00:09:55.830 --> 00:10:02.789
The Bible book of Acts, chapter 3, in verse 19 tells us that this involves repenting and

00:10:02.789 --> 00:10:10.549
turning around. In other words, to receive God's gift, which includes his mercy, we must adjust our

00:10:10.549 --> 00:10:17.350
thinking by repenting and then turn around by adjusting our conduct and course in life wherever

00:10:17.350 --> 00:10:25.190
necessary. The opportunity to do this is open to all people. As our Creator, God is not partial

00:10:25.190 --> 00:10:31.269
in His mercy, and in the friendship He offers. He has kindly put everything in place for us.

00:10:31.909 --> 00:10:37.269
All we must do is be grateful and humble, and then take the next step.

00:10:38.470 --> 00:10:46.389
That step involves accepting Jesus and His teachings. God requires that we follow the example of

00:10:46.389 --> 00:10:53.590
His Son. How closely must we do so? At John chapter 14 and verse 6, Jesus explained,

00:10:54.470 --> 00:11:03.750
I am the way and the truth and the life. No one comes to the Father except through me. No one.

00:11:04.870 --> 00:11:10.789
So then to come into God's friendship, we must follow His Son as true Christians.

00:11:11.509 --> 00:11:19.830
So far, we have reviewed how sin separated humans from God. Then we considered what God has done to

00:11:19.830 --> 00:11:25.990
heal the breach or close the gap so that we can come back into His favor as His friends.

00:11:26.789 --> 00:11:32.230
Now, let's look even further into what we must do, which brings us to the third key point.

00:11:32.950 --> 00:11:35.750
How can a person become God's friend?

00:11:36.710 --> 00:11:41.750
We invite you to consider what is said at James chapter 4 and verse 8.

00:11:42.389 --> 00:11:48.710
If you have a copy of the Bible, we urge you to follow along. James chapter 4 and verse 8.

00:11:49.509 --> 00:11:58.950
As we read it, please notice first the invitation, then the response, and finally what we must do.

00:11:59.509 --> 00:12:00.470
It reads,

00:12:13.909 --> 00:12:20.950
So first, what is the invitation? It is draw close to God. That is followed by what response on God's

00:12:20.950 --> 00:12:28.309
part. He will draw close to you. But for God to do this, what must we do to show that we accept

00:12:28.309 --> 00:12:36.789
His invitation? We must cleanse and purify ourselves according to His standards. This will take effort.

00:12:37.830 --> 00:12:43.269
For example, we must learn about His standards, and we must come to appreciate that they are the

00:12:43.269 --> 00:12:51.110
best for us, and then we must be determined to follow them. Above all, we do this because we want to

00:12:51.110 --> 00:12:58.950
please God and to be His friend. So then how can you develop a friendship with God, show initiative,

00:12:58.950 --> 00:13:05.110
and put forth the effort? Consider this. If you have a house plant, you know that it doesn't grow on

00:13:05.110 --> 00:13:11.190
its own. You have to water it regularly and keep it in an environment that helps it to grow. True?

00:13:12.389 --> 00:13:19.190
Something similar is true of our friendship with God. We nurture this friendship by reading and

00:13:19.190 --> 00:13:25.350
studying God's Word, the Bible. When we do so, we learn important things about God. For example,

00:13:25.350 --> 00:13:33.590
we learn that God's name is Jehovah. And as is true of any good friendship, it's important that we

00:13:33.590 --> 00:13:41.509
use His name. If we're sincere in our efforts to draw close to Him, as we read at James chapter 4

00:13:41.590 --> 00:13:51.350
verse 8, Jehovah will draw close to us. And He never abandons His true friends. In fact, John 17

00:13:51.350 --> 00:13:59.590
verse 3 tells us that coming to know God means everlasting life for us. What an undeserved kindness

00:13:59.590 --> 00:14:07.269
and priceless gift for Jehovah's true friends. So that you too can enjoy a bright future as God's

