We urge you to learn these things and to worship God in harmony with the truth that is revealed

00:14:45.669 --> 00:14:52.389
in His Word. So what important points have we considered regarding how a person can become God's

00:14:52.389 --> 00:14:59.909
friend? First, get to know God by reading and studying His Word. Jesus said that doing this means

00:14:59.909 --> 00:15:09.029
everlasting life and then learn about God's name and use it. Now we'll list four more things that

00:15:09.029 --> 00:15:17.350
those who desire to become God's friends must do. They are imitate God's qualities, reject

00:15:17.350 --> 00:15:23.029
thinking and actions that offend God, associate with those who want to be God's friends,

00:15:23.830 --> 00:15:31.029
and avoid friendship with people who ignore or mock God's standards. Now a few things in that list

00:15:31.029 --> 00:15:36.789
speak for themselves, don't they? Such as associate with those who want to be God's friend and

00:15:36.789 --> 00:15:42.470
avoid friendship with people who ignore or mock God's standards. That makes sense, doesn't it? Think

00:15:42.470 --> 00:15:47.909
back to our illustration about the house plant. You must not only water and nurture it,

00:15:48.549 --> 00:15:54.230
but you must keep it in the right environment, one that helps it to grow. Likewise,

00:15:54.230 --> 00:16:00.309
associating with those who also want to be God's friend is the right environment for us.

00:16:01.429 --> 00:16:07.509
But what about the requirement to imitate God's qualities? How can an imperfect people do this?

00:16:08.389 --> 00:16:13.909
Well, for a few minutes, we'll look at just two of God's qualities and how we can imitate Him.

00:16:14.549 --> 00:16:21.909
And we begin with God's love. An important way that we can imitate God's love and become his

00:16:21.909 --> 00:16:29.830
friend is by applying what his son Jesus taught us. For example, Jesus said, just as you want men to

00:16:29.830 --> 00:16:37.909
do to you, do the same way to them. A simple statement, but one that takes effort to apply, true.

00:16:38.710 --> 00:16:45.669
Can we do this? Yes. And a person who desires to be God's friend will put forth the effort needed

00:16:45.669 --> 00:16:53.350
to do this. To succeed in imitating God's love, we must try to see people as Jehovah sees them.

00:16:53.350 --> 00:16:58.710
We must try to put ourselves in the place of others so that we can understand their needs,

00:16:58.710 --> 00:17:05.910
their concerns, and even their pain of heart. Some may be challenged physically because of injury,

00:17:05.910 --> 00:17:12.950
disease, or aging. Others are coping with emotional trials because of depression or anxiety.

00:17:13.829 --> 00:17:19.589
Many people face difficulties that we have not experienced. For instance, a young person may

00:17:19.589 --> 00:17:25.349
find it hard to understand older people, and here she will really need to think about what it

00:17:25.349 --> 00:17:32.470
must be like to be an older person. If that is true of you, how can you imitate God's love?

00:17:33.430 --> 00:17:40.470
One important way is by listening carefully until you understand the other person's feelings.

00:17:40.470 --> 00:17:47.430
When you do so, you are in a better position to imitate God's love. Those who desire to

00:17:47.430 --> 00:17:54.950
be Jehovah's friends will be moved to imitate his love by acting according to what others really need.

00:17:55.750 --> 00:18:00.710
That brings us to a second and related quality that of kindness.

00:18:01.509 --> 00:18:07.990
Anyone who desires to be God's friend must be kind to others. Here again, we can learn much

00:18:07.990 --> 00:18:15.589
from what Jesus said and did. God's son said that the most high is kind toward the unthankful

00:18:15.589 --> 00:18:21.509
and wicked. Jesus appreciated this outstanding quality of his heavenly Father,

00:18:21.509 --> 00:18:26.470
and he imitated God's kindness. What helped Jesus to do so?

00:18:27.670 --> 00:18:34.390
He treated people in a kind manner by anticipating how his words and actions might affect their

00:18:34.390 --> 00:18:40.630
feelings. For example, the Bible tells us that a woman known to be a sinner approached Jesus,

00:18:41.349 --> 00:18:48.069
weeping and wetting his feet with her tears. Jesus discerned that she was repentant,

00:18:48.710 --> 00:18:53.509
and he knew how heartbroken she would be if he just dismissed her unkindly.

00:18:54.390 --> 00:19:01.029
Like his heavenly Father, Jesus looked for the good in her. We know this because he

00:19:01.029 --> 00:19:10.630
commended her, then he forgave her. Following Jesus example, how can we also imitate God's kindness?

00:19:11.430 --> 00:19:18.950
We can do so by being gentle to all people whenever possible. Kind people discern how to deal

00:19:18.950 --> 00:19:26.710
with delicate situations. Kind people avoid hurting the feelings of others. When we do this,

00:19:26.710 --> 00:19:34.950
we try to anticipate how our words and actions might affect them. That is how a true friend of God

00:19:35.029 --> 00:19:41.990
will treat others. Well, this review of just a few of Jehovah's many outstanding qualities

00:19:41.990 --> 00:19:48.470
gives us an idea of how much we can benefit from reading the Bible, and then applying its many

00:19:48.470 --> 00:19:57.109
lessons for us. Yes, friendship with God is possible, and we can imitate his outstanding qualities.

